  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced", 
    "date": "1997-06-24", 
    "text": "Civil Rights Act of 1997 - Allows any person aggrieved by an action of the Federal Government consisting of intentionally discriminating against, or granting a preference to, any person or group based in whole or in part on race, color, national origin, or sex to bring an action in a U.S. district court for appropriate relief (including back pay). Requires awarding a prevailing plaintiff attorney's fees as part of the costs. Defines \"preference\" as an advantage of any kind, including a quota, set-aside, numerical goal, timetable, or other numerical objective."
  }, 
